<p>WSBF is an FCC Class-A non-commercial radio station broadcasting at a frequency of 88.1 MHz. Our studio is at <a href="http://goo.gl/Ax9tF">315 Hendrix Center</a>, and our transmitter is located on <a href="http://goo.gl/N99yS">Kite Hill</a> in Clemson, SC.</p>
<p>Our transmitter has an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Effective_radiated_power">effective radiated power</a> of 3000 watts. It features an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radio_Data_System">RDS</a> encoder, which is used to broadcast the name and artist of each song played via a program written by Chief Engineer <a href="http://wsbf.net/users/odsquad64">Kevin Haag</a>.</p>
<p>The three WSBF Engineers include the Chief Engineer, the Computer Engineer, and the Equipment Engineer. The Chief and Computer Engineers are senior staff positions, and the Equipment Engineer is an intermediate staff position.</p>
<p>WSBF Engineering is now a Creative Inquiry. For more information, visit Clemson's <a href="http://www.clemson.edu/academics/programs/creative-inquiry/projects/current-projects.html?action=display&id=385">Creative Inquiry Page</a> or contact <a href="mailto:dbowman@clemson.edu">Prof. David Bowman</a>.